{% call getstarted.section("What is FTS?") -%}

  <p>The <strong>Flexible Template System</strong> (FTS) is a pattern system within Drupal that allows our <a href="https://www.redhat.com/en" target="_blank">redhat.com</a> web properties to scale. Users can leverage custom FTS patterns to design, build, or iterate pages while maintaining brand standards and design system consistency. We can play around with these pattern settings inside a prototyping tool called <strong>Patternkit</strong>. This is an incredibly power resource as it serves as both a development tool and library of all of our patterns.</p>

  <pfe-cta pfe-priority="secondary">
      <a href="https://source.redhat.com/departments/marketing/digitalmarketingstrategy/flexibletemplatingsystem" target="_blank">Learn how to use FTS</a>
  </pfe-cta>

  <pfe-cta style="margin-left:32px;">
    <a href="https://webrh-patternkit.int.open.paas.redhat.com/schema/pattern_page" target="_blank">Browse Patternkit patterns</a>
  </pfe-cta>

{%- endcall %}

{% call getstarted.section("What is Drupal?") -%}

  <p>Red Hat uses <strong>Drupal</strong>, the content management system. Over 30,000 pages were built with and are maintained in Drupal including support for eight different languages. As our web properties scale, it is vital to have a modern content management system that both designers and developers can use to build or iterate pages quickly. We offer a one-time three-hour training session to all new Drupal users and you are automatically enrolled in this session when you are granted Drupal access.</p>

  <pfe-cta pfe-priority="secondary">
      <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScKW_9M93PMmhm1ys4_7nG56mDhixrGfBEV15-exfePOzSOAQ/viewform" target="_blank">Request Drupal access</a>
  </pfe-cta>

{%- endcall %}

{% call getstarted.section("What is the FTS starter kit?") -%}

  <p>The <strong>FTS starter kit</strong> is the bridge between the Adobe XD design tool and the page building experience within Drupal. Sometimes designers are unsure of what FTS patterns are available to use or they are concerned about consistency when moving from a design to development environment. The FTS starter kit aims to eliminate inconsistencies by providing designers with customizable FTS patterns that are 1:1 when using those same patterns to build pages in Drupal.</p>

  <pfe-cta pfe-priority="secondary">
      <a href="https://xd.adobe.com/view/404ce962-da2d-444b-aa93-490a774e361c-151f/" target="_blank">Browse available patterns</a>
  </pfe-cta>

{%- endcall %}

{% call getstarted.section("What is Adobe XD?") -%}

  <p>The FTS starter kit was built in and is maintained in <strong>Adobe XD</strong>, it needs to be installed so you can take full advantage of customizing FTS patterns in a design environment before you build the page in Drupal. Once installed, your Adobe account needs to be enrolled in the <em>Adobe for Teams</em> plan in order for us to grant you access to the FTS starter kit or any other of our XD libraries. Please contact your manager for further assistance with enrolling in Adobe for Teams.</p>

  <pfe-cta pfe-priority="secondary">
      <a href="https://redhat.service-now.com/help?id=sc_cat_item&sys_id=488f88c3956221004c71bb9efe94def5" target="_blank">Request Adobe for Teams access</a>
  </pfe-cta>

  <pfe-cta style="margin-left:32px;">
    <a href="https://www.adobe.com/products/xd/learn/get-started.html" target="_blank">Learn how to use Adobe XD</a>
  </pfe-cta>

{%- endcall %}

